d between the "children of light" (Exilic Cubans) and the "children of darkness" (Resident Cubans). Examining the recent saga of the Elián González custody battle, he shows how the cultural construction of la lucha has become a distinctly Miami-style spirituality that makes el exilio (exile) the basis for religious reflection, understanding, and practice-and that conflates political mobilization with spiritual meaning in an ongoing confrontation with evil.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Apr 2020) 0aChristianity and politicsxFloridaxMiami. 0aChristianity and politicszFloridazMiami. 0aCuban AmericansxPolitics and governmentxFloridaxMiami. 0aCuban AmericansxReligionxFloridaxMiami. 0aCuban AmericansxSocial conditionsxFloridaxMiami. 0aCuban AmericanszFloridazMiamixPolitics and government. 0aCuban AmericanszFloridazMiamixReligion. 0aCuban AmericanszFloridazMiamixSocial conditions. 0aExilesxPolitical activityxFloridaxMiami. 0aExilesxPolitical activityzFloridazMiami. 0aExilesxReligious lifexFloridaxMiami. 0aExilesxReligious lifezFloridazMiami. 0aExilesxSocial conditionsxFloridaxMiami. 0aExileszFloridazMiamixSocial conditions. 0aOppression (Psychology)xPolitical aspectsxFloridaxMiami. 0aOppression (Psychology)xPolitical aspectszFloridazMiami. 7aRELIGION / Comparative Religion.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package 2000-2015z978311066334108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520930100423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520930100.jpg  a978-3-11-066334-1  UC Press eBook Package 2000-2015c2000d2015  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-d